{{Infobox website |logo = DailyBurn logo 2016.png |logo_size = 200px |commercial = Yes |type = Health/fitness |registration = Required |language = English |owner = [[IAC (company)|IAC]] |alexa = {{DecreasePositive}} 19,673 ({{as of|2014|4|1|alt=April 2014}})<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/dailyburn.com|title=Dailyburn.com Site Info|publisher=[[Alexa Internet]]|accessdate=March 26, 2018}}</ref><!--Updated monthly by OKBot.--> |name = DailyBurn |launch date = 2007 |current status = Operational }}
'''DailyBurn''' is a [[health and fitness]] company with a membership of approximately 2.5 million that provides workout and nutrition programs on a variety of web, mobile, and TV apps. DailyBurn streaming workout videos are led by [[Personal trainer|master trainers]] and produced by Mason Bendewald, the director of [[Beachbody]]'s [[P90X]] workout program. [[IAC (company)|IAC]] holds a majority stake in the company.
The website has an [[Apple Inc.|Apple]] [[iPhone]] and an [[Apple TV]] application which was a January App of the Week in ''[[The New York Times]]'' technology section.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/01/07/technology/personaltech/07app.html|author=Roy Furchgott|title=App of the Week: Recording Your Daily Bread|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=January 6, 2010|accessdate=May 26, 2018}}</ref> It was also named one of the top 100 websites of 2010 by [[PC Mag]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.pcmag.com/slideshow_viewer/0,1205,l=253515&a=253510&po=97,00.asp?p=n|title=DailyBurn|magazine=[[PC Magazine]]|accessdate=May 26, 2018}}</ref>
==Company history== DailyBurn was founded in 2007 by Andy Smith and Stephen Blankenship. DailyBurn was accepted into [[Techstars|TechStars]] Boulder in the summer of 2008. In 2009, the site changed its name and [[Uniform Resource Locator|URL]] from Gyminee to DailyBurn.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://andrewhy.de/gyminee-is-now-daily-burn/|author=Andrew Hyde|title=Gyminee is now Daily Burn|accessdate=May 26, 2018}}</ref> IAC acquired a majority stake of DailyBurn in May 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2010/05/20/iac-dailyburn/|title=IAC Buys Into Fitness Social Network DailyBurn|publisher=[[TechCrunch]]|date=May 20, 2010|accessdate=May 26, 2018}}</ref> The company established headquarters in the [[Frank Gehry]] designed IAC building, along the West Side Highway in the [[Chelsea, Manhattan|Chelsea]] neighborhood of [[Manhattan]]. DailyBurn's first product, an exercise and nutrition tracking app, was rebranded as DailyBurn Tracker in December 2011 and the company's new streaming workout video app was given the name DailyBurn.
In 2016, Daily Burn launched ''Daily Burn 365'', a live, daily fitness show.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/daily-burn-launches-daily-live-fitness-show-300198397.html|title=Daily Burn Launches Daily Live Fitness Show|publisher=[[Cision]]|date=January 4, 2016|accessdate=May 26, 2018}}</ref>
==Production== Some DailyBurn videos are directed and produced by Executive Producer Mason Bendewald. Daily Burn 365 is produced by Zack McTee for Allegory Productions and created with Chris Vivion and Matthew Mills at Spacestation.
The following trainers and health experts have appeared in DailyBurn videos:
*Anja Garcia *Cody Storey *Ben Booker *Judi Brown *[[Eitan Kramer]] *Keaira LaShae *J.R. Rogers *Brionhy Smyth *Justin Rubin
